definitions.definition: A small depression in the pitch caused by batsmen tapping their bats on the point where they have taken block .
The approximate place where the toe of the bat touches the pitch when a batsman is taking guard.

main_definition: ( cricket ) A small depression in the pitch caused by batsmen tapping their bats on the point where they have taken block .
secondary_definitions: ( by extension ) The approximate place where the toe of the bat touches the pitch when a batsman is taking guard.
